 ******************************************************************************
 ******            BiCAS - Bidlo's Cellular Automata Simulator          *******
 ******************************************************************************

                           (c) Michal Bidlo, BUT FIT
                        http://www.fit.vutbr.cz/~bidlom

 ******************************************************************************

This program requires the Python environment with NumPy and PyGame libraries
installed. An up-to-date Linux-like OS is strongly preferred.

To run an example, enter a selected subdirectory containing .tab files and run:

./BiCAS.py

or

python BiCAS.py

and follow the help notes shown by BiCAS.


To play with CAs, add, remove or modify the rules in .tab files or create your
own! The file default.cas allows specifying a custom initial CA configuration,
the original one means that a single cell (centered in the CA lattice) will be
in state 1 (a seed cell), all the other cells will be in state 0 by default.

Enjoy!
